views with users, police officers, judges, and parents and friends of addicts in one West Virginia town, William Garriott finds that this overriding effort to confront the problem changed the character of the community as well as the role of law in creating and maintaining social order. Ultimately, this work addresses the impact of methamphetamine and, more generally, the war on drugs, on everyday life in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aDrug trafficxInvestigationxWest Virginia. 0aDrug trafficxInvestigationzWest Virginia. 0aMethamphetamine abusexPolitical aspectsxUnited States. 0aMethamphetamine abusexPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aMethamphetamine abusexPreventionxWest Virginia. 0aMethamphetamine abusezWest VirginiaxPrevention. 0aMethamphetaminexWest Virginia. 0aMethamphetaminezWest Virginia. 0aPolicexUnited States. 0aPolicezUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814733004423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814733004.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK